The paper deals with image-to-image translation, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new model that can utilize both paired and unpaired training data, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the comparison of their proposed method with two strong baselines, which involves experimental evaluation (cs.GR). Finally, the paper deals with image processing techniques, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
